title: San Diego Bus Network: Routing & Wait-Time Simulation
description: Merged GTFS stops, trips, and schedules to build a detailed timetable; mapped lines on an interactive map; used BFS to find stop-to-stop routes; and simulated bus arrivals and passenger wait times to analyze service patterns and transit efficiency.

title: Deer Pendants
description: Worked with artisans to 3D design and metal smith deer pendants .

title: Loan Analytics: Cleaning, Visualization, Taxes & Paradox
description: Cleaned loan records (dates/terms/titles), computed correlations, visualized interest rates by FICO band and term, ran a permutation test on personal‐statement effects, built federal/state tax brackets to estimate disposable income, and aggregated outcomes to surface a Simpson’s paradox example.

title: Recipes and Ratings Analysis
description: Analyzed recipes containing nutrition facts and user ratings to explore whether a recipe’s carbohydrate content correlates with its total calories

title: Bunny Sweater Launch
description: Designed, sourced, and launched a sweater; 41 preorders and $1.5k profit.

title: Image Processing Suite: RGB Ops, Premium Filters & KNN Classifier
description: Implemented an RGB image class with safe getters/setters and helpers, a template + standard/premium processors (negate, grayscale, rotate, brightness, blur, tiling, sticker, edge highlight), and a KNN image classifier with Euclidean distance—complete with doctests, I/O helpers, and cost/coupon logic.

title: TikTok Algorithm and Adolescent Mental Health
description: Analyzed how TikTok’s recommendation system influences adolescent body image and anxiety by combining survey data with TikTok Research API metrics. Conducted regression, permutation, and sentiment analyses to examine correlations between exposure to fashion, fitness, and nutrition content and symptoms of body dysmorphia. Addressed data ethics through anonymization, consent, and bias mitigation, contributing to the hypothesis, ethics, and discussion sections.
